Articles.Content:
It's not working for me... Running 0.25 on x64. Installed the mod and music files in the correct folder, double checked that. The mod does create the file 'settings.cfg', but my music is not listed.

Edited November 13, 2014 by CJJackR
Is this mod still in active development? I`m waiting for context specific music before I download...

Is this mod still in active development? I`m waiting for context specific music before I download...

Version 3 is coming along nicely. I've been focusing on it rather than bug fixes for v2 as this is a major re-write and most of those bugs will be irrelevant.

There's still a ways to go, but here's what I'm working on at the moment:

Playlists are still defined in .cfg files at this stage. Here's an example:

playlist
{
	name = "Mun"
	loop = true
	shuffle = true
	fade = fadeOut
	tracks
	{
		"Frost Waltz"
		"Frost Waltz (Alternate)"
	}
	playWhen
	{
		body = Mun
		situation = ORBITING
	}
}

Version 3 is coming along nicely. I've been focusing on it rather than bug fixes for v2 as this is a major re-write and most of those bugs will be irrelevant.

There's still a ways to go, but here's what I'm working on at the moment:

http://i.imgur.com/LRFbA4B.png

Playlists are still defined in .cfg files at this stage. Here's an example:

playlist
{
    name = "Mun"
    loop = true
    shuffle = true
    fade = fadeOut
    tracks
    {
        "Frost Waltz"
        "Frost Waltz (Alternate)"
    }
    playWhen
    {
        body = Mun
        situation = ORBITING
    }
}
When I run this on x64 none of the mp3 files I put in music are detected, and when I run x86 only about half of them. Does anyone know what could be causing this?
